# History: ci-release-pipeline-must-mirror-required-pr-gate

This file records the version history of
`ci-release-pipeline-must-mirror-required-pr-gate`.

## v1.0.0 (2026-07-01)

**What changed:** Initial creation of the skill.

**Why:** ProjectHephaestus issue #1499 — audit finding [S12 Packaging]: `release.yml`
ran only `pixi run pytest tests/unit` before publishing to PyPI, while the required PR
gate (`_required.yml` `integration-tests`) ran the integration-only suites
(`test_sdist_contents.py`, `test_package_import.py`, `test_cli_entry_points.py`) on every
PR. A `workflow_dispatch` release against an arbitrary commit BYPASSES that merged-PR
guarantee, so the integration suite could be entirely skipped on the manual publish path.

The durable, generalizable lessons captured:

1. A merged-PR safety guarantee does NOT extend to `workflow_dispatch`/manual triggers —
   the release/publish pipeline must run the SAME required gate itself.
2. Reuse the already-wired gate; do NOT add a new CI job. The release `test` job was
   already `needs`-ed by `build-and-publish` and already ran `pixi run dev-install`, so
   adding a STEP to it (not a parallel job) gates the publish with zero wiring changes.
3. Mirror the required gate's invocation VERBATIM, including `--override-ini="addopts="`
   (escape the unit-coverage addopts) and `--strict-markers` (safe because the marker is
   registered) — a variant invocation risks behavioral drift.
4. Verification proof pattern: prove the named integration guards are actually COLLECTED
   (`--collect-only -q | grep <guards>`) and that the build-backend-dependent sdist test
   does NOT silently skip in the release env.

**Verification:** verified-local — the integration suite passed locally exactly as the
release step invokes it (372 passed, 1 skipped; sdist-contents test 2 passed, not
skipped). CI on the PR was pending at capture time. Considered amending
`architecture-executable-convention-guard-pattern` (which already carries the
"reuse the already-wired gate" convention) but the release-pipeline-vs-required-PR-gate
parity / `workflow_dispatch`-bypass lesson is a distinct, focused theme, so a new skill
was created to keep it discoverable.
